🔹 What is a Servlet?

A Servlet is a Java class that:

Handles HTTP requests
Processes them
Sends back HTTP responses

It runs inside a web server like:
Apache Tomcat
Jetty

Behind the scenes:

Browser sends HTTP request
Server receives it
Servlet processes it
Servlet sends response back

Spring Boot runs on a servlet container like:
👉 Apache Tomcat (embedded)

And Spring uses a special servlet called:
👉 DispatcherServlet

This servlet:

Receives all HTTP requests
Decides which controller method to call
Sends response back

So even if you don’t see it, servlet is always there.

A servlet container:

Manages servlet lifecycle
Handles request routing
Manages threads
Manages sessions
Ex: Apache Tomcat

Browser → asks for data
Servlet → acts like receptionist
Database → data storage

